  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "Registration of Israel\u2019s Troops"
      content: "A year after Israel\u2019s departure from Egypt, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spoke to Moses in the Tabernacle[COMMENT[0]] in the wilderness of Sinai.
        On the first day of the second month[COMMENT[1]] of that year he said, "
      comments:
      - number: '1:1a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Tent of Meeting.
      - number: '1:1b '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in April or
            May.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFrom the whole community of Israel, record the names of all
        the warriors by their clans and families. List all the men "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'twenty years old or older who are able to go to war. You and Aaron
        must register the troops, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and you will be assisted by one family leader from each tribe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese are the tribes and the names of the leaders who will
        assist you:Reuben\n\tElizur son of Shedeur"
      comments: []
    - title: Leader
      content: "Simeon\n\tShelumiel son of Zurishaddai"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah\n\tNahshon son of Amminadab"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Issachar\n\tNethanel son of Zuar"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Zebulun\n\tEliab son of Helon"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ephraim son of Joseph\n\tElishama son of Ammihud\n\tManasseh son
        of Joseph\n\tGamaliel son of Pedahzur"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Benjamin\n\tAbidan son of Gideoni"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dan\n\tAhiezer son of Ammishaddai"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Asher\n\tPagiel son of Ocran"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gad\n\tEliasaph son of Deuel"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Naphtali\n\tAhira son of Enan      "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These are the chosen leaders of the community, the leaders of their
        ancestral tribes, the heads of the clans of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses and Aaron called together these chosen leaders, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and they assembled the whole community of Israel on that very day.[COMMENT[0]]
        All the people were registered according to their ancestry by their clans
        and families. The men of Israel who were twenty years old or older were listed
        one by one, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'on the first day of the second month; '
        - ft: see 1:1.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses. So Moses
        recorded their names in the wilderness of Sinai.  This is the number of men
        twenty years old or older who were able to go to war, as their names were
        listed in the records of their clans and families[COMMENT[0]]:Reuben (Jacob\u2019s[COMMENT[1]]oldest
        son)\n\t46,500Simeon\n\t59,300Gad\n\t45,650Judah\n\t74,600Issachar\n\t54,400Zebulun\n\t57,400Ephraim
        son of Joseph\n\t40,500Manasseh son of Joseph\n\t32,200Benjamin\n\t35,400Dan\n\t62,700Asher\n\t41,500Naphtali\n\t53,400      "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20-21a '
        contents:
        - ft: In the Hebrew text, this sentence (
          body: This is the number of men twenty years old or older who were able
            to go to war, as their names were listed in the records of their clans
            and families
        - ft: ) is repeated in 1:22, 24, 26, 28, 30, 32, 34, 36, 38, 40, 42.
          body: 
      - number: '1:20-21b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "Israel\u2019s. "
        - ft: "The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged
            throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes to the individual patriarch
            and sometimes to the nation."
          body: 
    - title: Number
      content: 'These were the men registered by Moses and Aaron and the twelve leaders
        of Israel, all listed according to their ancestral descent. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were registered by families\u2014all the men of Israel who were
        twenty years old or older and able to go to war. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The total number was 603,550.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But this total did not include the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not include the tribe of Levi in the registration; do not
        count them with the rest of the Israelites. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Put the Levites in charge of the Tabernacle of the Covenant,[COMMENT[0]]
        along with all its furnishings and equipment. They must carry the Tabernacle
        and all its furnishings as you travel, and they must take care of it and
        camp around it. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:50 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'Tabernacle of the Testimony; '
        - ft: also in 1:53.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Whenever it is time for the Tabernacle to move, the Levites will
        take it down. And when it is time to stop, they will set it up again. But
        any unauthorized person who goes too near the Tabernacle must be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each tribe of Israel will camp in a designated area with its own
        family banner. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the Levites will camp around the Tabernacle of the Covenant to
        protect the community of Israel from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger. The Levites are responsible to stand guard around the Tabernacle.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: So the Israelites did everything just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Organization for Israel\u2019s Camp"
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave these instructions to Moses
        and Aaron: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the Israelites set up camp, each tribe will be assigned
        its own area. The tribal divisions will camp beneath their family banners
        on all four sides of the Tabernacle,[COMMENT[0]] but at some distance from
        it.  \u201CThe divisions of Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun are to camp toward
        the sunrise on the east side of the Tabernacle, beneath their family banners.
        These are the names of the tribes, their leaders, and the numbers of their
        registered troops:Judah\n\tNahshon son of Amminadab\n\t74,600Issachar\n\tNethanel
        son of Zuar\n\t54,400Zebulun\n\tEliab son of Helon\n\t57,400      "
      comments:
      - number: '2:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 2:17.
          body: 
    - title: Number
      content: "So the total of all the troops on Judah\u2019s side of the camp is
        186,400. These three tribes are to lead the way whenever the Israelites travel
        to a new campsite.  \u201CThe divisions of Reuben, Simeon, and Gad are to
        camp on the south side of the Tabernacle, beneath their family banners. These
        are the names of the tribes, their leaders, and the numbers of their registered
        troops:Reuben\n\tElizur son of Shedeur\n\t46,500Simeon\n\tShelumiel son of
        Zurishaddai\n\t59,300Gad\n\tEliasaph son of Deuel[COMMENT[0]]45,650      "
      comments:
      - number: '2:14-15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in many Hebrew manuscripts, Samaritan Pentateuch, and Latin Vulgate
            (see also 1:14); most Hebrew manuscripts read '
          body: son of Reuel.
    - title: Number
      content: "So the total of all the troops on Reuben\u2019s side of the camp
        is 151,450. These three tribes will be second in line whenever the Israelites
        travel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the Tabernacle, carried by the Levites, will set out from
        the middle of the camp. All the tribes are to travel in the same order that
        they camp, each in position under the appropriate family banner.  \u201CThe
        divisions of Ephraim, Manasseh, and Benjamin are to camp on the west side
        of the Tabernacle, beneath their family banners. These are the names of the
        tribes, their leaders, and the numbers of their registered troops:Ephraim\n\tElishama
        son of Ammihud\n\t40,500Manasseh\n\tGamaliel son of Pedahzur\n\t32,200Benjamin\n\tAbidan
        son of Gideoni\n\t35,400      "
      comments: []
    - title: Number
      content: "So the total of all the troops on Ephraim\u2019s side of the camp
        is 108,100. These three tribes will be third in line whenever the Israelites
        travel.  \u201CThe divisions of Dan, Asher, and Naphtali are to camp on the
        north side of the Tabernacle, beneath their family banners. These are the
        names of the tribes, their leaders, and the numbers of their registered troops:Dan\n\tAhiezer
        son of Ammishaddai\n\t62,700Asher\n\tPagiel son of Ocran\n\t41,500Naphtali\n\tAhira
        son of Enan\n\t53,400      "
      comments: []
    - title: Number
      content: "So the total of all the troops on Dan\u2019s side of the camp is
        157,600. These three tribes will be last, marching under their banners whenever
        the Israelites travel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In summary, the troops of Israel listed by their families totaled
        603,550. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded, the Levites
        were not included in this registration. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: So the people of Israel did everything as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded Moses. Each clan and family set up camp and marched under their
        banners exactly as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had instructed them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Levites Appointed for Service
      content: 'This is the family line of Aaron and Moses as it was recorded when
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Moses on Mount Sinai: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The names of Aaron\u2019s sons were Nadab (the oldest), Abihu, Eleazar,
        and Ithamar. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These sons of Aaron were anointed and ordained to minister as priests. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Nadab and Abihu died in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence in the wilderness of Sinai when they burned before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        the wrong kind of fire, different than he had commanded. Since they had no
        sons, this left only Eleazar and Ithamar to serve as priests with their father,
        Aaron.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCall forward the tribe of Levi, and present them to Aaron the
        priest to serve as his assistants. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will serve Aaron and the whole community, performing their sacred
        duties in and around the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: around the Tent of Meeting, doing service at the Tabernacle.
    - title: 
      content: 'They will also maintain all the furnishings of the sacred tent,[COMMENT[0]]
        serving in the Tabernacle on behalf of all the Israelites. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 3:25.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Assign the Levites to Aaron and his sons. They have been given from
        among all the people of Israel to serve as their assistants. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Appoint Aaron and his sons to carry out the duties of the priesthood.
        But any unauthorized person who goes too near the sanctuary must be put to
        death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I have chosen the Levites from among the Israelites to
        serve as substitutes for all the firstborn sons of the people of Israel.
        The Levites belong to me, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for all the firstborn males are mine. On the day I struck down all
        the firstborn sons of the Egyptians, I set apart for myself all the firstborn
        in Israel, both of people and of animals. They are mine; I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Registration of the Levites
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke again to Moses in the wilderness
        of Sinai. He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRecord the names of the members of the tribe of Levi by their
        families and clans. List every male who is one month old or older.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses listed them, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Levi had three sons, whose names were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The clans descended from Gershon were named after two of his descendants,
        Libni and Shimei.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The clans descended from Kohath were named after four of his descendants,
        Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The clans descended from Merari were named after two of his descendants,
        Mahli and Mushi.\n\tThese were the Levite clans, listed according to their
        family groups.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon were composed of the clans descended from
        Libni and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There were 7,500 males one month old or older among these Gershonite
        clans. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were assigned the area to the west of the Tabernacle for their
        camp. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The leader of the Gershonite clans was Eliasaph son of Lael. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These two clans were responsible to care for the Tabernacle, including
        the sacred tent with its layers of coverings, the curtain at its entrance, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the curtains of the courtyard that surrounded the Tabernacle and
        altar, the curtain at the courtyard entrance, the ropes, and all the equipment
        related to their use.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of Kohath were composed of the clans descended from
        Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There were 8,600[COMMENT[0]] males one month old or older among these
        Kohathite clans. They were responsible for the care of the sanctuary, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:28 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some Greek manuscripts read '
          body: '8,300; '
        - ft: see total in 3:39.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'and they were assigned the area south of the Tabernacle for their
        camp. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The leader of the Kohathite clans was Elizaphan son of Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These four clans were responsible for the care of the Ark, the table,
        the lampstand, the altars, the various articles used in the sanctuary, the
        inner curtain, and all the equipment related to their use. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, was the chief administrator over
        all the Levites, with special responsibility for the oversight of the sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of Merari were composed of the clans descended from
        Mahli and Mushi. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There were 6,200 males one month old or older among these Merarite
        clans. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were assigned the area north of the Tabernacle for their camp.
        The leader of the Merarite clans was Zuriel son of Abihail. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These two clans were responsible for the care of the frames supporting
        the Tabernacle, the crossbars, the pillars, the bases, and all the equipment
        related to their use. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were also responsible for the posts of the courtyard and all
        their bases, pegs, and ropes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The area in front of the Tabernacle, in the east toward the sunrise,[COMMENT[0]]
        was reserved for the tents of Moses and of Aaron and his sons, who had the
        final responsibility for the sanctuary on behalf of the people of Israel.
        Anyone other than a priest or Levite who went too near the sanctuary was
        to be put to death.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:38 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: toward the sunrise, in front of the Tent of Meeting.
    - title: 
      content: "When Moses and Aaron counted the Levite clans at the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        command, the total number was 22,000 males one month old or older.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Redeeming the Firstborn Sons
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CNow count
        all the firstborn sons in Israel who are one month old or older, and make
        a list of their names. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Levites must be reserved for me as substitutes for the firstborn
        sons of Israel; I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. And the Levites\u2019
        livestock must be reserved for me as substitutes for the firstborn livestock
        of the whole nation of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses counted the firstborn sons of the people of Israel, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The number of firstborn sons who were one month old or older was
        22,273.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake the Levites as substitutes for the firstborn sons of the
        people of Israel. And take the livestock of the Levites as substitutes for
        the firstborn livestock of the people of Israel. The Levites belong to me;
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There are 273 more firstborn sons of Israel than there are Levites.
        To redeem these extra firstborn sons, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'collect five pieces of silver[COMMENT[0]] for each of them (each
        piece weighing the same as the sanctuary shekel, which equals twenty gerahs). '
      comments:
      - number: '3:47 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '5 shekels '
        - ft: '[2 ounces or 57 grams].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Give the silver to Aaron and his sons as the redemption price for
        the extra firstborn sons.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses collected the silver for redeeming the firstborn sons of
        Israel who exceeded the number of Levites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He collected 1,365 pieces of silver[COMMENT[0]] on behalf of these
        firstborn sons of Israel (each piece weighing the same as the sanctuary shekel). '
      comments:
      - number: '3:50 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1,365 [shekels] of silver '
        - ft: '[34 pounds or 15.5 kilograms].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: And Moses gave the silver for the redemption to Aaron and his sons,
        just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Duties of the Kohathite Clan
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRecord the names of the members of the clans and families of
        the Kohathite division of the tribe of Levi. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'List all the men between the ages of thirty and fifty who are eligible
        to serve in the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 4:4, 15, 23, 25, 28, 30, 31, 33, 35, 37, 39, 41, 43, 47.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe duties of the Kohathites at the Tabernacle will relate
        to the most sacred objects. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the camp moves, Aaron and his sons must enter the Tabernacle
        first to take down the inner curtain and cover the Ark of the Covenant[COMMENT[0]]
        with it. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Ark of the Testimony.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they must cover the inner curtain with fine goatskin leather
        and spread over that a single piece of blue cloth. Finally, they must put
        the carrying poles of the Ark in place.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNext they must spread a blue cloth over the table where the
        Bread of the Presence is displayed, and on the cloth they will place the
        bowls, ladles, jars, pitchers, and the special bread. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must spread a scarlet cloth over all of this, and finally a
        covering of fine goatskin leather on top of the scarlet cloth. Then they
        must insert the carrying poles into the table.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNext they must cover the lampstand with a blue cloth, along
        with its lamps, lamp snuffers, trays, and special jars of olive oil. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they must cover the lampstand and its accessories with fine
        goatskin leather and place the bundle on a carrying frame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNext they must spread a blue cloth over the gold incense altar
        and cover this cloth with fine goatskin leather. Then they must attach the
        carrying poles to the altar. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must take all the remaining furnishings of the sanctuary and
        wrap them in a blue cloth, cover them with fine goatskin leather, and place
        them on the carrying frame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey must remove the ashes from the altar for sacrifices and
        cover the altar with a purple cloth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the altar utensils\u2014the firepans, meat forks, shovels, basins,
        and all the containers\u2014must be placed on the cloth, and a covering of
        fine goatskin leather must be spread over them. Finally, they must put the
        carrying poles in place. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The camp will be ready to move when Aaron and his sons have finished
        covering the sanctuary and all the sacred articles. The Kohathites will come
        and carry these things to the next destination. But they must not touch the
        sacred objects, or they will die. So these are the things from the Tabernacle
        that the Kohathites must carry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEleazar son of Aaron the priest will be responsible for the
        oil of the lampstand, the fragrant incense, the daily grain offering, and
        the anointing oil. In fact, Eleazar will be responsible for the entire Tabernacle
        and everything in it, including the sanctuary and its furnishings.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not let the Kohathite clans be destroyed from among the
        Levites! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what you must do so they will live and not die when they
        approach the most sacred objects. Aaron and his sons must always go in with
        them and assign a specific duty or load to each person. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Kohathites must never enter the sanctuary to look at the sacred
        objects for even a moment, or they will die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Duties of the Gershonite Clan
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRecord the names of the members of the clans and families of
        the Gershonite division of the tribe of Levi. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'List all the men between the ages of thirty and fifty who are eligible
        to serve in the Tabernacle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese Gershonite clans will be responsible for general service
        and carrying loads. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must carry the curtains of the Tabernacle, the Tabernacle itself
        with its coverings, the outer covering of fine goatskin leather, and the
        curtain for the Tabernacle entrance. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are also to carry the curtains for the courtyard walls that
        surround the Tabernacle and altar, the curtain across the courtyard entrance,
        the ropes, and all the equipment related to their use. The Gershonites are
        responsible for all these items. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Aaron and his sons will direct the Gershonites regarding all their
        duties, whether it involves moving the equipment or doing other work. They
        must assign the Gershonites responsibility for the loads they are to carry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So these are the duties assigned to the Gershonite clans at the Tabernacle.
        They will be directly responsible to Ithamar son of Aaron the priest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Duties of the Merarite Clan
      content: "\u201CNow record the names of the members of the clans and families
        of the Merarite division of the tribe of Levi. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'List all the men between the ages of thirty and fifty who are eligible
        to serve in the Tabernacle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTheir only duty at the Tabernacle will be to carry loads. They
        will carry the frames of the Tabernacle, the crossbars, the posts, and the
        bases; "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'also the posts for the courtyard walls with their bases, pegs, and
        ropes; and all the accessories and everything else related to their use.
        Assign the various loads to each man by name. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So these are the duties of the Merarite clans at the Tabernacle.
        They are directly responsible to Ithamar son of Aaron the priest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Summary of the Registration
      content: 'So Moses, Aaron, and the other leaders of the community listed the
        members of the Kohathite division by their clans and families. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The list included all the men between thirty and fifty years of age
        who were eligible for service in the Tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the total number came to 2,750. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So this was the total of all those from the Kohathite clans who were
        eligible to serve at the Tabernacle. Moses and Aaron listed them, just as
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded through Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Gershonite division was also listed by its clans and families. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The list included all the men between thirty and fifty years of age
        who were eligible for service in the Tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the total number came to 2,630. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So this was the total of all those from the Gershonite clans who
        were eligible to serve at the Tabernacle. Moses and Aaron listed them, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Merarite division was also listed by its clans and families. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The list included all the men between thirty and fifty years of age
        who were eligible for service in the Tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the total number came to 3,200. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So this was the total of all those from the Merarite clans who were
        eligible for service. Moses and Aaron listed them, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded through Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses, Aaron, and the leaders of Israel listed all the Levites
        by their clans and families. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the men between thirty and fifty years of age who were eligible
        for service in the Tabernacle and for its transportation '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'numbered 8,580. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When their names were recorded, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded through Moses, each man was assigned his task and told what
        to carry.\n\tAnd so the registration was completed, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
