  - verses:
    - title: "Purity in Israel\u2019s Camp"
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave these instructions to Moses: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCommand the people of Israel to remove from the camp anyone
        who has a skin disease[COMMENT[0]] or a discharge, or who has become ceremonially
        unclean by touching a dead person. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Traditionally rendered '
          body: 'leprosy. '
        - ft: The Hebrew word used here describes various skin diseases.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "This command applies to men and women alike. Remove them so they
        will not defile the camp in which I live among them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the Israelites did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        Moses and removed such people from the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel: If
        any of the people\u2014men or women\u2014betray the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by doing wrong to another person, they are guilty. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must confess their sin and make full restitution for what they
        have done, adding an additional 20 percent and returning it to the person
        who was wronged. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if the person who was wronged is dead, and there are no near
        relatives to whom restitution can be made, the payment belongs to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and must be given to the priest. Those who are guilty must also bring a ram
        as a sacrifice, and they will be purified and made right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: bring a ram for atonement, which will make atonement for them.
    - title: 
      content: 'All the sacred offerings that the Israelites bring to a priest will
        belong to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each priest may keep all the sacred donations that he receives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Protecting Marital Faithfulness
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\n\t\u201CSuppose
        a man\u2019s wife goes astray, and she is unfaithful to her husband "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and has sex with another man, but neither her husband nor anyone
        else knows about it. She has defiled herself, even though there was no witness
        and she was not caught in the act. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If her husband becomes jealous and is suspicious of his wife and
        needs to know whether or not she has defiled herself, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the husband must bring his wife to the priest. He must also bring
        an offering of two quarts[COMMENT[0]] of barley flour to be presented on
        her behalf. Do not mix it with olive oil or frankincense, for it is a jealousy
        offering\u2014an offering to prove whether or not she is guilty.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1/10 of an ephah '
        - ft: '[2.2 liters].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe priest will then present her to stand trial before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He must take some holy water in a clay jar and pour into it dust
        he has taken from the Tabernacle floor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the priest has presented the woman before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        he must unbind her hair and place in her hands the offering of proof\u2014the
        jealousy offering to determine whether her husband\u2019s suspicions are
        justified. The priest will stand before her, holding the jar of bitter water
        that brings a curse to those who are guilty. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priest will then put the woman under oath and say to her, \u2018If
        no other man has had sex with you, and you have not gone astray and defiled
        yourself while under your husband\u2019s authority, may you be immune from
        the effects of this bitter water that brings on the curse. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you have gone astray by being unfaithful to your husband,
        and have defiled yourself by having sex with another man\u2014\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAt this point the priest must put the woman under oath by saying,
        \u2018May the people know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        curse is upon you when he makes you infertile, causing your womb to shrivel[COMMENT[0]]
        and your abdomen to swell. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: when he causes your thigh to waste away.
    - title: 
      content: "Now may this water that brings the curse enter your body and cause
        your abdomen to swell and your womb to shrivel.[COMMENT[0]]\u2019 And the
        woman will be required to say, \u2018Yes, let it be so.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '5:22 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: and your thigh to waste away.
    - title: 
      content: 'And the priest will write these curses on a piece of leather and
        wash them off into the bitter water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will make the woman drink the bitter water that brings on the
        curse. When the water enters her body, it will cause bitter suffering if
        she is guilty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe priest will take the jealousy offering from the woman\u2019s
        hand, lift it up before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, and carry it
        to the altar. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will take a handful of the flour as a token portion and burn it
        on the altar, and he will require the woman to drink the water. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If she has defiled herself by being unfaithful to her husband, the
        water that brings on the curse will cause bitter suffering. Her abdomen will
        swell and her womb will shrink,[COMMENT[0]] and her name will become a curse
        among her people. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:27 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: and her thigh will waste away.
    - title: 
      content: 'But if she has not defiled herself and is pure, then she will be
        unharmed and will still be able to have children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is the ritual law for dealing with suspicion. If a woman
        goes astray and defiles herself while under her husband\u2019s authority, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "or if a man becomes jealous and is suspicious that his wife has been
        unfaithful, the husband must present his wife before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and the priest will apply this entire ritual law to her. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The husband will be innocent of any guilt in this matter, but his
        wife will be held accountable for her sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Nazirite Laws
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\n\t\u201CIf
        any of the people, either men or women, take the special vow of a Nazirite,
        setting themselves apart to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in a special
        way, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they must give up wine and other alcoholic drinks. They must not
        use vinegar made from wine or from other alcoholic drinks, they must not
        drink fresh grape juice, and they must not eat grapes or raisins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As long as they are bound by their Nazirite vow, they are not allowed
        to eat or drink anything that comes from a grapevine\u2014not even the grape
        seeds or skins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey must never cut their hair throughout the time of their
        vow, for they are holy and set apart to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        Until the time of their vow has been fulfilled, they must let their hair
        grow long. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they must not go near a dead body during the entire period of
        their vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if the dead person is their own father, mother, brother, or
        sister, they must not defile themselves, for the hair on their head is the
        symbol of their separation to God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This requirement applies as long as they are set apart to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf someone falls dead beside them, the hair they have dedicated
        will be defiled. They must wait for seven days and then shave their heads.
        Then they will be cleansed from their defilement. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On the eighth day they must bring two turtledoves or two young pigeons
        to the priest at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 6:13, 18.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'The priest will offer one of the birds for a sin offering and the
        other for a burnt offering. In this way, he will purify them[COMMENT[0]]
        from the guilt they incurred through contact with the dead body. Then they
        must reaffirm their commitment and let their hair begin to grow again. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: make atonement for them.
    - title: 
      content: 'The days of their vow that were completed before their defilement
        no longer count. They must rededicate themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a Nazirite for the full term of their vow, and each must bring a one-year-old
        male lamb for a guilt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is the ritual law for Nazirites. At the conclusion of
        their time of separation as Nazirites, they must each go to the entrance
        of the Tabernacle "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and offer their sacrifices to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t:
        a one-year-old male lamb without defect for a burnt offering, a one-year-old
        female lamb without defect for a sin offering, a ram without defect for a
        peace offering, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "a basket of bread made without yeast\u2014cakes of choice flour mixed
        with olive oil and wafers spread with olive oil\u2014along with their prescribed
        grain offerings and liquid offerings. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priest will present these offerings before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t:
        first the sin offering and the burnt offering; "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then the ram for a peace offering, along with the basket of bread
        made without yeast. The priest must also present the prescribed grain offering
        and liquid offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the Nazirites will shave their heads at the entrance of
        the Tabernacle. They will take the hair that had been dedicated and place
        it on the fire beneath the peace-offering sacrifice. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the Nazirite\u2019s head has been shaved, the priest will take
        for each of them the boiled shoulder of the ram, and he will take from the
        basket a cake and a wafer made without yeast. He will put them all into the
        Nazirite\u2019s hands. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the priest will lift them up as a special offering before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. These are holy portions for the priest,
        along with the breast of the special offering and the thigh of the sacred
        offering that are lifted up before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. After
        this ceremony the Nazirites may again drink wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is the ritual law of the Nazirites, who vow to bring these
        offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. They may also bring additional
        offerings if they can afford it. And they must be careful to do whatever
        they vowed when they set themselves apart as Nazirites.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Priestly Blessing
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell Aaron and his sons to bless the people of Israel with
        this special blessing:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless you\n\tand protect
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> smile on you\n\tand be gracious
        to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> show you his favor\n\tand give
        you his peace.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whenever Aaron and his sons bless the people of Israel in my name,
        I myself will bless them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
