  - verses:
    - title: Preparing the Lamps
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive Aaron the following instructions: When you set up the
        seven lamps in the lampstand, place them so their light shines forward in
        front of the lampstand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Aaron did this. He set up the seven lamps so they reflected their
        light forward, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The entire lampstand, from its base to its decorative blossoms, was
        made of beaten gold. It was built according to the exact design the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had shown Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Levites Dedicated
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow set the Levites apart from the rest of the people of Israel
        and make them ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do this by sprinkling them with the water of purification, and have
        them shave their entire body and wash their clothing. Then they will be ceremonially
        clean. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have them bring a young bull and a grain offering of choice flour
        moistened with olive oil, along with a second young bull for a sin offering. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then assemble the whole community of Israel, and present the Levites
        at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 8:15, 19, 22, 24, 26.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "When you present the Levites before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the people of Israel must lay their hands on them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Raising his hands, Aaron must then present the Levites to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a special offering from the people of Israel, thus dedicating them to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s service.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNext the Levites will lay their hands on the heads of the young
        bulls. Present one as a sin offering and the other as a burnt offering to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, to purify the Levites and make them
        right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to make atonement for the Levites.
    - title: 
      content: "Then have the Levites stand in front of Aaron and his sons, and raise
        your hands and present them as a special offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In this way, you will set the Levites apart from the rest of the
        people of Israel, and the Levites will belong to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After this, they may go into the Tabernacle to do their work, because
        you have purified them and presented them as a special offering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COf all the people of Israel, the Levites are reserved for me.
        I have claimed them for myself in place of all the firstborn sons of the
        Israelites; I have taken the Levites as their substitutes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For all the firstborn males among the people of Israel are mine,
        both of people and of animals. I set them apart for myself on the day I struck
        down all the firstborn sons of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, I have claimed the Levites in place of all the firstborn sons
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And of all the Israelites, I have assigned the Levites to Aaron and
        his sons. They will serve in the Tabernacle on behalf of the Israelites and
        make sacrifices to purify[COMMENT[0]] the people so no plague will strike
        them when they approach the sanctuary.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:19 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: make atonement for.
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses, Aaron, and the whole community of Israel dedicated the
        Levites, carefully following all the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        instructions to Moses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Levites purified themselves from sin and washed their clothes,
        and Aaron lifted them up and presented them to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a special offering. He then offered a sacrifice to purify them and make
        them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:21 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: then made atonement for them to purify them.
    - title: 
      content: 'After that the Levites went into the Tabernacle to perform their
        duties, assisting Aaron and his sons. So they carried out all the commands
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Moses concerning the Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also instructed Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is the rule the Levites must follow: They must begin serving
        in the Tabernacle at the age of twenty-five, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and they must retire at the age of fifty. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After retirement they may assist their fellow Levites by serving
        as guards at the Tabernacle, but they may not officiate in the service. This
        is how you must assign duties to the Levites.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Second Passover
      content: "A year after Israel\u2019s departure from Egypt, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai. In the first month[COMMENT[0]]
        of that year he said, "
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: The first month of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar usually occurs
            within the months of March and April.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell the Israelites to celebrate the Passover at the prescribed
        time, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "at twilight on the fourteenth day of the first month.[COMMENT[0]]
        Be sure to follow all my decrees and regulations concerning this celebration.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late March,
            April, or early May.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses told the people to celebrate the Passover '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'in the wilderness of Sinai as twilight fell on the fourteenth day
        of the month. And they celebrated the festival there, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But some of the men had been ceremonially defiled by touching a dead
        body, so they could not celebrate the Passover that day. They came to Moses
        and Aaron that day '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and said, \u201CWe have become ceremonially unclean by touching a
        dead body. But why should we be prevented from presenting the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        offering at the proper time with the rest of the Israelites?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses answered, \u201CWait here until I have received instructions
        for you from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This was the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s reply to Moses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel: If
        any of the people now or in future generations are ceremonially unclean at
        Passover time because of touching a dead body, or if they are on a journey
        and cannot be present at the ceremony, they may still celebrate the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Passover. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They must offer the Passover sacrifice one month later, at twilight
        on the fourteenth day of the second month.[COMMENT[0]] They must eat the
        Passover lamb at that time with bitter salad greens and bread made without
        yeast. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late April,
            May, or early June.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'They must not leave any of the lamb until the next morning, and they
        must not break any of its bones. They must follow all the normal regulations
        concerning the Passover.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut those who neglect to celebrate the Passover at the regular
        time, even though they are ceremonially clean and not away on a trip, will
        be cut off from the community of Israel. If they fail to present the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        offering at the proper time, they will suffer the consequences of their guilt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if foreigners living among you want to celebrate the Passover
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, they must follow these same decrees
        and regulations. The same laws apply both to native-born Israelites and to
        the foreigners living among you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Fiery Cloud
      content: 'On the day the Tabernacle was set up, the cloud covered it.[COMMENT[0]]
        But from evening until morning the cloud over the Tabernacle looked like
        a pillar of fire. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:15 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: covered the Tabernacle, the Tent of the Testimony.
    - title: 
      content: "This was the regular pattern\u2014at night the cloud that covered
        the Tabernacle had the appearance of fire. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whenever the cloud lifted from over the sacred tent, the people of
        Israel would break camp and follow it. And wherever the cloud settled, the
        people of Israel would set up camp. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In this way, they traveled and camped at the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        command wherever he told them to go. Then they remained in their camp as
        long as the cloud stayed over the Tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If the cloud remained over the Tabernacle for a long time, the Israelites
        stayed and performed their duty to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sometimes the cloud would stay over the Tabernacle for only a few
        days, so the people would stay for only a few days, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded. Then at the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s command they
        would break camp and move on. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sometimes the cloud stayed only overnight and lifted the next morning.
        But day or night, when the cloud lifted, the people broke camp and moved
        on. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whether the cloud stayed above the Tabernacle for two days, a month,
        or a year, the people of Israel stayed in camp and did not move on. But as
        soon as it lifted, they broke camp and moved on. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they camped or traveled at the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        command, and they did whatever the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told them
        through Moses."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Silver Trumpets
      content: 'Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMake two trumpets of hammered silver for calling the community
        to assemble and for signaling the breaking of camp. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When both trumpets are blown, everyone must gather before you at
        the entrance of the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Tent of Meeting.
    - title: 
      content: "But if only one trumpet is blown, then only the leaders\u2014the
        heads of the clans of Israel\u2014must present themselves to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you sound the signal to move on, the tribes camped on
        the east side of the Tabernacle must break camp and move forward. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you sound the signal a second time, the tribes camped on the
        south will follow. You must sound short blasts as the signal for moving on. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when you call the people to an assembly, blow the trumpets with
        a different signal. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Only the priests, Aaron\u2019s descendants, are allowed to blow the
        trumpets. This is a permanent law for you, to be observed from generation
        to generation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you arrive in your own land and go to war against your
        enemies who attack you, sound the alarm with the trumpets. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God will remember you and rescue you from your enemies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Blow the trumpets in times of gladness, too, sounding them at your
        annual festivals and at the beginning of each month. And blow the trumpets
        over your burnt offerings and peace offerings. The trumpets will remind your
        God of his covenant with you. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Israelites Leave Sinai
      content: "In the second year after Israel\u2019s departure from Egypt\u2014on
        the twentieth day of the second month[COMMENT[0]]\u2014the cloud lifted from
        the Tabernacle of the Covenant.[COMMENT[1]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11a '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late April,
            May, or early June.
          body: 
      - number: '10:11b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Tabernacle of the Testimony.
    - title: 
      content: 'So the Israelites set out from the wilderness of Sinai and traveled
        on from place to place until the cloud stopped in the wilderness of Paran.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the people set out for the first time, following the instructions
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given through Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah\u2019s troops led the way. They marched behind their banner,
        and their leader was Nahshon son of Amminadab. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were joined by the troops of the tribe of Issachar, led by Nethanel
        son of Zuar, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the troops of the tribe of Zebulun, led by Eliab son of Helon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Tabernacle was taken down, and the Gershonite and Merarite
        divisions of the Levites were next in the line of march, carrying the Tabernacle
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Reuben\u2019s troops went next, marching behind their banner. Their
        leader was Elizur son of Shedeur. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were joined by the troops of the tribe of Simeon, led by Shelumiel
        son of Zurishaddai, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the troops of the tribe of Gad, led by Eliasaph son of Deuel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Next came the Kohathite division of the Levites, carrying the sacred
        objects from the Tabernacle. Before they arrived at the next camp, the Tabernacle
        would already be set up at its new location. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ephraim\u2019s troops went next, marching behind their banner. Their
        leader was Elishama son of Ammihud. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were joined by the troops of the tribe of Manasseh, led by Gamaliel
        son of Pedahzur, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the troops of the tribe of Benjamin, led by Abidan son of Gideoni.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dan\u2019s troops went last, marching behind their banner and serving
        as the rear guard for all the tribal camps. Their leader was Ahiezer son
        of Ammishaddai. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were joined by the troops of the tribe of Asher, led by Pagiel
        son of Ocran, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the troops of the tribe of Naphtali, led by Ahira son of Enan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This was the order in which the Israelites marched, division by division.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day Moses said to his brother-in-law, Hobab son of Reuel the
        Midianite, \u201CWe are on our way to the place the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        promised us, for he said, \u2018I will give it to you.\u2019 Come with us
        and we will treat you well, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has promised
        wonderful blessings for Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Hobab replied, \u201CNo, I will not go. I must return to my own
        land and family.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPlease don\u2019t leave us,\u201D Moses pleaded. \u201CYou
        know the places in the wilderness where we should camp. Come, be our guide. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you do, we\u2019ll share with you all the blessings the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gives us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They marched for three days after leaving the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        with the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Covenant moving
        ahead of them to show them where to stop and rest. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they moved on each day, the cloud of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        hovered over them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And whenever the Ark set out, Moses would shout, \u201CArise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and let your enemies be scattered! Let them flee before you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when the Ark was set down, he would say, \u201CReturn, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        to the countless thousands of Israel!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The People Complain to Moses
      content: "Soon the people began to complain about their hardship, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        heard everything they said. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        anger blazed against them, and he sent a fire to rage among them, and he
        destroyed some of the people in the outskirts of the camp. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the people screamed to Moses for help, and when he prayed to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, the fire stopped. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After that, the area was known as Taberah (which means \u201Cthe
        place of burning\u201D), because fire from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had burned among them there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the foreign rabble who were traveling with the Israelites began
        to crave the good things of Egypt. And the people of Israel also began to
        complain. \u201COh, for some meat!\u201D they exclaimed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWe remember the fish we used to eat for free in Egypt. And
        we had all the cucumbers, melons, leeks, onions, and garlic we wanted. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now our appetites are gone. All we ever see is this manna!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The manna looked like small coriander seeds, and it was pale yellow
        like gum resin. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people would go out and gather it from the ground. They made
        flour by grinding it with hand mills or pounding it in mortars. Then they
        boiled it in a pot and made it into flat cakes. These cakes tasted like pastries
        baked with olive oil. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The manna came down on the camp with the dew during the night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Moses heard all the families standing in the doorways of their tents
        whining, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> became extremely angry. Moses
        was also very aggravated. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Moses said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, \u201CWhy
        are you treating me, your servant, so harshly? Have mercy on me! What did
        I do to deserve the burden of all these people? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Did I give birth to them? Did I bring them into the world? Why did
        you tell me to carry them in my arms like a mother carries a nursing baby?
        How can I carry them to the land you swore to give their ancestors? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where am I supposed to get meat for all these people? They keep whining
        to me, saying, \u2018Give us meat to eat!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I can\u2019t carry all these people by myself! The load is far too
        heavy! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If this is how you intend to treat me, just go ahead and kill me.
        Do me a favor and spare me this misery!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Moses Chooses Seventy Leaders
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CGather
        before me seventy men who are recognized as elders and leaders of Israel.
        Bring them to the Tabernacle[COMMENT[0]] to stand there with you. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:16 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Tent of Meeting.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will come down and talk to you there. I will take some of the Spirit
        that is upon you, and I will put the Spirit upon them also. They will bear
        the burden of the people along with you, so you will not have to carry it
        alone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd say to the people, \u2018Purify yourselves, for tomorrow
        you will have meat to eat. You were whining, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        heard you when you cried, \u201COh, for some meat! We were better off in
        Egypt!\u201D Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give you meat, and
        you will have to eat it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And it won\u2019t be for just a day or two, or for five or ten or
        even twenty. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will eat it for a whole month until you gag and are sick of it.
        For you have rejected the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, who is here among
        you, and you have whined to him, saying, \u201CWhy did we ever leave Egypt?\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moses responded to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, \u201CThere
        are 600,000 foot soldiers here with me, and yet you say, \u2018I will give
        them meat for a whole month!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even if we butchered all our flocks and herds, would that satisfy
        them? Even if we caught all the fish in the sea, would that be enough?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CHas my
        arm lost its power? Now you will see whether or not my word comes true!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses went out and reported the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        words to the people. He gathered the seventy elders and stationed them around
        the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the tent; '
        - ft: also in 11:26.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came down in the cloud and spoke
        to Moses. Then he gave the seventy elders the same Spirit that was upon Moses.
        And when the Spirit rested upon them, they prophesied. But this never happened
        again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Two men, Eldad and Medad, had stayed behind in the camp. They were
        listed among the elders, but they had not gone out to the Tabernacle. Yet
        the Spirit rested upon them as well, so they prophesied there in the camp. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A young man ran and reported to Moses, \u201CEldad and Medad are
        prophesying in the camp!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Joshua son of Nun, who had been Moses\u2019 assistant since his youth,
        protested, \u201CMoses, my master, make them stop!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moses replied, \u201CAre you jealous for my sake? I wish that
        all the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s people were prophets and that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> would put his Spirit upon them all!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Moses returned to the camp with the elders of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: ' Sends Quail'
      content: 'Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent a wind that brought quail
        from the sea and let them fall all around the camp. For miles in every direction
        there were quail flying about three feet above the ground.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:31 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'there were quail about 3 feet '
        - ft: '[2 cubits or 92 centimeters] '
          body: deep on the ground.
    - title: 
      content: 'So the people went out and caught quail all that day and throughout
        the night and all the next day, too. No one gathered less than fifty bushels[COMMENT[0]]!
        They spread the quail all around the camp to dry. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:32 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '10 homers '
        - ft: '[2.2 kiloliters].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "But while they were gorging themselves on the meat\u2014while it
        was still in their mouths\u2014the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        blazed against the people, and he struck them with a severe plague. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So that place was called Kibroth-hattaavah (which means \u201Cgraves
        of gluttony\u201D) because there they buried the people who had craved meat
        from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: From Kibroth-hattaavah the Israelites traveled to Hazeroth, where
        they stayed for some time.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Complaints of Miriam and Aaron
      content: 'While they were at Hazeroth, Miriam and Aaron criticized Moses because
        he had married a Cushite woman. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said, \u201CHas the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoken only
        through Moses? Hasn\u2019t he spoken through us, too?\u201D But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        heard them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "(Now Moses was very humble\u2014more humble than any other person
        on earth.)  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So immediately the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called to Moses, Aaron,
        and Miriam and said, \u201CGo out to the Tabernacle,[COMMENT[0]] all three
        of you!\u201D So the three of them went to the Tabernacle. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Tent of Meeting.
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> descended in the pillar of cloud
        and stood at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]] \u201CAaron and
        Miriam!\u201D he called, and they stepped forward. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the tent; '
        - ft: also in 12:10.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to them, \u201CNow listen
        to what I say:\n\t\u201CIf there were prophets among you,\n\tI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        would reveal myself in visions.\n\tI would speak to them in dreams.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But not with my servant Moses.\n\tOf all my house, he is the one
        I trust.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I speak to him face to face,\n\tclearly, and not in riddles!\n\tHe
        sees the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as he is.\n\tSo why were you not afraid\n\tto
        criticize my servant Moses?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was very angry with them, and he
        departed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the cloud moved from above the Tabernacle, there stood Miriam,
        her skin as white as snow from leprosy.[COMMENT[0]] When Aaron saw what had
        happened to her, '
      comments:
      - number: '12:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'with a skin disease. '
        - ft: The Hebrew word used here can describe various skin diseases.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "he cried out to Moses, \u201COh, my master! Please don\u2019t punish
        us for this sin we have so foolishly committed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let her be like a stillborn baby, already decayed at birth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, \u201CO
        God, I beg you, please heal her!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CIf her father
        had done nothing more than spit in her face, wouldn\u2019t she be defiled
        for seven days? So keep her outside the camp for seven days, and after that
        she may be accepted back.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Miriam was kept outside the camp for seven days, and the people
        waited until she was brought back before they traveled again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Then they left Hazeroth and camped in the wilderness of Paran.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Twelve Scouts Explore Canaan
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> now said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSend out men to explore the land of Canaan, the land I am giving
        to the Israelites. Send one leader from each of the twelve ancestral tribes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded him. He
        sent out twelve men, all tribal leaders of Israel, from their camp in the
        wilderness of Paran. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These were the tribes and the names of their leaders:Reuben\n\tShammua
        son of Zaccur"
      comments: []
    - title: Leader
      content: "Simeon\n\tShaphat son of Hori"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah\n\tCaleb son of Jephunneh"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Issachar\n\tIgal son of Joseph"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ephraim\n\tHoshea son of Nun"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Benjamin\n\tPalti son of Raphu"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Zebulun\n\tGaddiel son of Sodi"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Manasseh son of Joseph\n\tGaddi son of Susi"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dan\n\tAmmiel son of Gemalli"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Asher\n\tSethur son of Michael"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Naphtali\n\tNahbi son of Vophsi"
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gad\n\tGeuel son of Maki      "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These are the names of the men Moses sent out to explore the land.
        (Moses called Hoshea son of Nun by the name Joshua.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Moses gave the men these instructions as he sent them out to explore
        the land: \u201CGo north through the Negev into the hill country. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See what the land is like, and find out whether the people living
        there are strong or weak, few or many. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See what kind of land they live in. Is it good or bad? Do their towns
        have walls, or are they unprotected like open camps? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is the soil fertile or poor? Are there many trees? Do your best to
        bring back samples of the crops you see.\u201D (It happened to be the season
        for harvesting the first ripe grapes.)  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they went up and explored the land from the wilderness of Zin
        as far as Rehob, near Lebo-hamath. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Going north, they passed through the Negev and arrived at Hebron,
        where Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai\u2014all descendants of Anak\u2014lived.
        (The ancient town of Hebron was founded seven years before the Egyptian city
        of Zoan.) "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they came to the valley of Eshcol, they cut down a branch with
        a single cluster of grapes so large that it took two of them to carry it
        on a pole between them! They also brought back samples of the pomegranates
        and figs. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That place was called the valley of Eshcol (which means \u201Ccluster\u201D),
        because of the cluster of grapes the Israelite men cut there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Scouting Report
      content: 'After exploring the land for forty days, the men returned '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to Moses, Aaron, and the whole community of Israel at Kadesh in the
        wilderness of Paran. They reported to the whole community what they had seen
        and showed them the fruit they had taken from the land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This was their report to Moses: \u201CWe entered the land you sent
        us to explore, and it is indeed a bountiful country\u2014a land flowing with
        milk and honey. Here is the kind of fruit it produces. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the people living there are powerful, and their towns are large
        and fortified. We even saw giants there, the descendants of Anak! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Amalekites live in the Negev, and the Hittites, Jebusites, and
        Amorites live in the hill country. The Canaanites live along the coast of
        the Mediterranean Sea[COMMENT[0]] and along the Jordan Valley.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:29 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the sea.
    - title: 
      content: "But Caleb tried to quiet the people as they stood before Moses. \u201CLet\u2019s
        go at once to take the land,\u201D he said. \u201CWe can certainly conquer
        it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the other men who had explored the land with him disagreed. \u201CWe
        can\u2019t go up against them! They are stronger than we are!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they spread this bad report about the land among the Israelites:
        \u201CThe land we traveled through and explored will devour anyone who goes
        to live there. All the people we saw were huge. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We even saw giants[COMMENT[0]] there, the descendants of Anak. Next
        to them we felt like grasshoppers, and that\u2019s what they thought, too!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '13:33 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: nephilim.
  - verses:
    - title: The People Rebel
      content: 'Then the whole community began weeping aloud, and they cried all
        night. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their voices rose in a great chorus of protest against Moses and
        Aaron. \u201CIf only we had died in Egypt, or even here in the wilderness!\u201D
        they complained. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> taking us to this country
        only to have us die in battle? Our wives and our little ones will be carried
        off as plunder! Wouldn\u2019t it be better for us to return to Egypt?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they plotted among themselves, \u201CLet\u2019s choose a new
        leader and go back to Egypt!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron fell face down on the ground before the whole
        community of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Two of the men who had explored the land, Joshua son of Nun and Caleb
        son of Jephunneh, tore their clothing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said to all the people of Israel, \u201CThe land we traveled
        through and explored is a wonderful land! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is pleased with us, he will
        bring us safely into that land and give it to us. It is a rich land flowing
        with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not rebel against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, and don\u2019t
        be afraid of the people of the land. They are only helpless prey to us! They
        have no protection, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is with us! Don\u2019t
        be afraid of them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the whole community began to talk about stoning Joshua and Caleb.
        Then the glorious presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to
        all the Israelites at the Tabernacle.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the Tent of Meeting.
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CHow long
        will these people treat me with contempt? Will they never believe me, even
        after all the miraculous signs I have done among them? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will disown them and destroy them with a plague. Then I will make
        you into a nation greater and mightier than they are!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Moses Intercedes for the People
      content: "But Moses objected. \u201CWhat will the Egyptians think when they
        hear about it?\u201D he asked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201CThey
        know full well the power you displayed in rescuing your people from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now if you destroy them, the Egyptians will send a report to the
        inhabitants of this land, who have already heard that you live among your
        people. They know, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, that you have appeared
        to your people face to face and that your pillar of cloud hovers over them.
        They know that you go before them in the pillar of cloud by day and the pillar
        of fire by night. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now if you slaughter all these people with a single blow, the nations
        that have heard of your fame will say, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was not able to bring them
        into the land he swore to give them, so he killed them in the wilderness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPlease, Lord, prove that your power is as great as you have
        claimed. For you said, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is slow to anger and filled
        with unfailing love, forgiving every kind of sin and rebellion. But he does
        not excuse the guilty. He lays the sins of the parents upon their children;
        the entire family is affected\u2014even children in the third and fourth
        generations.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In keeping with your magnificent, unfailing love, please pardon the
        sins of this people, just as you have forgiven them ever since they left
        Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CI will pardon them
        as you have requested. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But as surely as I live, and as surely as the earth is filled with
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s glory, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'not one of these people will ever enter that land. They have all
        seen my glorious presence and the miraculous signs I performed both in Egypt
        and in the wilderness, but again and again they have tested me by refusing
        to listen to my voice. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will never even see the land I swore to give their ancestors.
        None of those who have treated me with contempt will ever see it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But my servant Caleb has a different attitude than the others have.
        He has remained loyal to me, so I will bring him into the land he explored.
        His descendants will possess their full share of that land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now turn around, and don\u2019t go on toward the land where the Amalekites
        and Canaanites live. Tomorrow you must set out for the wilderness in the
        direction of the Red Sea.[COMMENT[0]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: sea of reeds.
    - title: ' Punishes the Israelites'
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long must I put up with this wicked community and its complaints
        about me? Yes, I have heard the complaints the Israelites are making against
        me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now tell them this: \u2018As surely as I live, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        I will do to you the very things I heard you say. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will all drop dead in this wilderness! Because you complained
        against me, every one of you who is twenty years old or older and was included
        in the registration will die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will not enter and occupy the land I swore to give you. The only
        exceptions will be Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018You said your children would be carried off as plunder.
        Well, I will bring them safely into the land, and they will enjoy what you
        have despised. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as for you, you will drop dead in this wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And your children will be like shepherds, wandering in the wilderness
        for forty years. In this way, they will pay for your faithlessness, until
        the last of you lies dead in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018Because your men explored the land for forty days, you
        must wander in the wilderness for forty years\u2014a year for each day, suffering
        the consequences of your sins. Then you will discover what it is like to
        have me for an enemy.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, have spoken! I will certainly
        do these things to every member of the community who has conspired against
        me. They will be destroyed here in this wilderness, and here they will die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The ten men Moses had sent to explore the land\u2014the ones who
        incited rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with their bad
        report\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "were struck dead with a plague before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Of the twelve who had explored the land, only Joshua and Caleb remained
        alive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Moses reported the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s words
        to all the Israelites, the people were filled with grief. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they got up early the next morning and went to the top of the
        range of hills. \u201CLet\u2019s go,\u201D they said. \u201CWe realize that
        we have sinned, but now we are ready to enter the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has promised us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moses said, \u201CWhy are you now disobeying the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        orders to return to the wilderness? It won\u2019t work. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not go up into the land now. You will only be crushed by your
        enemies because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is not with you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you face the Amalekites and Canaanites in battle, you will be
        slaughtered. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will abandon you because you
        have abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people defiantly pushed ahead toward the hill country, even
        though neither Moses nor the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        Covenant left the camp. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Then the Amalekites and the Canaanites who lived in those hills came
        down and attacked them and chased them back as far as Hormah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Laws concerning Offerings
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\n\t\u201CWhen
        you finally settle in the land I am giving you, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "you will offer special gifts as a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        These gifts may take the form of a burnt offering, a sacrifice to fulfill
        a vow, a voluntary offering, or an offering at any of your annual festivals,
        and they may be taken from your herds of cattle or your flocks of sheep and
        goats. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you present these offerings, you must also give the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        a grain offering of two quarts[COMMENT[0]] of choice flour mixed with one
        quart[COMMENT[1]] of olive oil. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:4a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1/10 of an ephah '
        - ft: '[2.2 liters].'
          body: 
      - number: '15:4b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1/4 of a hin '
        - ft: '[1 liter]; also in 15:5.'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'For each lamb offered as a burnt offering or a special sacrifice,
        you must also present one quart of wine as a liquid offering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf the sacrifice is a ram, give a grain offering of four quarts[COMMENT[0]]
        of choice flour mixed with a third of a gallon[COMMENT[1]] of olive oil, "
      comments:
      - number: '15:6a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '2/10 of an ephah '
        - ft: '[4.4 liters].'
          body: 
      - number: '15:6b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1/3 of a hin '
        - ft: '[1.3 liters]; also in 15:7.'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "and give a third of a gallon of wine as a liquid offering. This will
        be a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you present a young bull as a burnt offering or as a sacrifice
        to fulfill a vow or as a peace offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you must also give a grain offering of six quarts[COMMENT[0]] of
        choice flour mixed with two quarts[COMMENT[1]] of olive oil, '
      comments:
      - number: '15:9a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '3/10 of an ephah '
        - ft: '[6.6 liters].'
          body: 
      - number: '15:9b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1/2 of a hin '
        - ft: '[2 liters]; also in 15:10.'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "and give two quarts of wine as a liquid offering. This will be a
        special gift, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEach sacrifice of a bull, ram, lamb, or young goat should be
        prepared in this way. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Follow these instructions with each offering you present. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All of you native-born Israelites must follow these instructions
        when you offer a special gift as a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if any foreigners visit you or live among you and want to present
        a special gift as a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        they must follow these same procedures. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Native-born Israelites and foreigners are equal before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and are subject to the same decrees. This is a permanent law for you, to
        be observed from generation to generation. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The same instructions and regulations will apply both to you and
        to the foreigners living among you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\n\t\u201CWhen
        you arrive in the land where I am taking you, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and you eat the crops that grow there, you must set some aside as
        a sacred offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Present a cake from the first of the flour you grind, and set it
        aside as a sacred offering, as you do with the first grain from the threshing
        floor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Throughout the generations to come, you are to present a sacred offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> each year from the first of your ground
        flour.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose you unintentionally fail to carry out all these
        commands that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given you through Moses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And suppose your descendants in the future fail to do everything
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded through Moses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If the mistake was made unintentionally, and the community was unaware
        of it, the whole community must present a young bull for a burnt offering
        as a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. It must be offered
        along with its prescribed grain offering and liquid offering and with one
        male goat for a sin offering. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "With it the priest will purify the whole community of Israel, making
        them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,[COMMENT[0]] and they
        will be forgiven. For it was an unintentional sin, and they have corrected
        it with their offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2014the special
        gift and the sin offering. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:25 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: will make atonement for the whole community of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'The whole community of Israel will be forgiven, including the foreigners
        living among you, for all the people were involved in the sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf one individual commits an unintentional sin, the guilty
        person must bring a one-year-old female goat for a sin offering. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The priest will sacrifice it to purify[COMMENT[0]] the guilty person
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, and that person will be forgiven. "
      comments:
      - number: '15:28 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to make atonement for.
    - title: 
      content: 'These same instructions apply both to native-born Israelites and
        to the foreigners living among you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut those who brazenly violate the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        will, whether native-born Israelites or foreigners, have blasphemed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and they must be cut off from the community. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since they have treated the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        word with contempt and deliberately disobeyed his command, they must be completely
        cut off and suffer the punishment for their guilt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Penalty for Breaking the Sabbath
      content: 'One day while the people of Israel were in the wilderness, they discovered
        a man gathering wood on the Sabbath day. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people who found him doing this took him before Moses, Aaron,
        and the rest of the community. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They held him in custody because they did not know what to do with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CThe man
        must be put to death! The whole community must stone him outside the camp.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the whole community took the man outside the camp and stoned him
        to death, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Tassels on Clothing
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel: Throughout
        the generations to come you must make tassels for the hems of your clothing
        and attach them with a blue cord. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you see the tassels, you will remember and obey all the commands
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> instead of following your own desires
        and defiling yourselves, as you are prone to do. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The tassels will help you remember that you must obey all my commands
        and be holy to your God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God who brought you out
        of the land of Egypt that I might be your God. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Korah\u2019s Rebellion"
      content: 'One day Korah son of Izhar, a descendant of Kohath son of Levi, conspired
        with Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, and On son of Peleth, from the
        tribe of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They incited a rebellion against Moses, along with 250 other leaders
        of the community, all prominent members of the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They united against Moses and Aaron and said, \u201CYou have gone
        too far! The whole community of Israel has been set apart by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        and he is with all of us. What right do you have to act as though you are
        greater than the rest of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s people?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Moses heard what they were saying, he fell face down on the
        ground. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to Korah and his followers, \u201CTomorrow morning the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will show us who belongs to him[COMMENT[0]] and
        who is holy. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will allow only those whom he
        selects to enter his own presence. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek version reads '
          body: 'God has visited and knows those who are his. '
        - ft: Compare 2 Tim 2:19.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Korah, you and all your followers must prepare your incense burners. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Light fires in them tomorrow, and burn incense before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        Then we will see whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> chooses as his holy
        one. You Levites are the ones who have gone too far!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses spoke again to Korah: \u201CNow listen, you Levites! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does it seem insignificant to you that the God of Israel has chosen
        you from among all the community of Israel to be near him so you can serve
        in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s Tabernacle and stand before
        the people to minister to them? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Korah, he has already given this special ministry to you and your
        fellow Levites. Are you now demanding the priesthood as well? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the one you and your followers
        are really revolting against! For who is Aaron that you are complaining about
        him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses summoned Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab, but they
        replied, \u201CWe refuse to come before you! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isn\u2019t it enough that you brought us out of Egypt, a land flowing
        with milk and honey, to kill us here in this wilderness, and that you now
        treat us like your subjects? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What\u2019s more, you haven\u2019t brought us into another land flowing
        with milk and honey. You haven\u2019t given us a new homeland with fields
        and vineyards. Are you trying to fool these men?[COMMENT[0]] We will not
        come.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:14 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Are you trying to put out the eyes of these men?
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses became very angry and said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        \u201CDo not accept their grain offerings! I have not taken so much as a
        donkey from them, and I have never hurt a single one of them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Moses said to Korah, \u201CYou and all your followers must come
        here tomorrow and present yourselves before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        Aaron will also be here. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You and each of your 250 followers must prepare an incense burner
        and put incense on it, so you can all present them before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        Aaron will also bring his incense burner.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So each of these men prepared an incense burner, lit the fire, and
        placed incense on it. Then they all stood at the entrance of the Tabernacle[COMMENT[0]]
        with Moses and Aaron. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:18 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the Tent of Meeting; '
        - ft: also in 16:19, 42, 43, 50.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, Korah had stirred up the entire community against Moses
        and Aaron, and they all gathered at the Tabernacle entrance. Then the glorious
        presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to the whole community, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet away from all these people so that I may instantly destroy
        them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moses and Aaron fell face down on the ground. \u201CO God,\u201D
        they pleaded, \u201Cyou are the God who gives breath to all creatures. Must
        you be angry with all the people when only one man sins?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen tell all the people to get away from the tents of Korah,
        Dathan, and Abiram.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses got up and rushed over to the tents of Dathan and Abiram,
        followed by the elders of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CQuick!\u201D he told the people. \u201CGet away from the tents
        of these wicked men, and don\u2019t touch anything that belongs to them.
        If you do, you will be destroyed for their sins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So all the people stood back from the tents of Korah, Dathan, and
        Abiram. Then Dathan and Abiram came out and stood at the entrances of their
        tents, together with their wives and children and little ones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Moses said, \u201CThis is how you will know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent me to do all these things that I have done\u2014for I have not done
        them on my own. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If these men die a natural death, or if nothing unusual happens,
        then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not sent me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does something entirely new
        and the ground opens its mouth and swallows them and all their belongings,
        and they go down alive into the grave,[COMMENT[0]] then you will know that
        these men have shown contempt for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:30 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'into Sheol; '
        - ft: also in 16:33.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'He had hardly finished speaking the words when the ground suddenly
        split open beneath them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth opened its mouth and swallowed the men, along with their
        households and all their followers who were standing with them, and everything
        they owned. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they went down alive into the grave, along with all their belongings.
        The earth closed over them, and they all vanished from among the people of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the people around them fled when they heard their screams. \u201CThe
        earth will swallow us, too!\u201D they cried. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then fire blazed forth from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and burned
        up the 250 men who were offering incense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  [COMMENT[1]]And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '16:36 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 16:36-50 are numbered 17:1-15 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell Eleazar son of Aaron the priest to pull all the incense
        burners from the fire, for they are holy. Also tell him to scatter the burning
        coals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Take the incense burners of these men who have sinned at the cost
        of their lives, and hammer the metal into a thin sheet to overlay the altar.
        Since these burners were used in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence, they have become holy. Let them serve as a warning to the people
        of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Eleazar the priest collected the 250 bronze incense burners that
        had been used by the men who died in the fire, and the bronze was hammered
        into a thin sheet to overlay the altar. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This would warn the Israelites that no unauthorized person\u2014no
        one who was not a descendant of Aaron\u2014should ever enter the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        presence to burn incense. If anyone did, the same thing would happen to him
        as happened to Korah and his followers. So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        instructions to Moses were carried out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the very next morning the whole community of Israel began muttering
        again against Moses and Aaron, saying, \u201CYou have killed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the community gathered to protest against Moses and Aaron, they
        turned toward the Tabernacle and saw that the cloud had covered it, and the
        glorious presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Moses and Aaron came and stood in front of the Tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet away from all these people so that I can instantly destroy
        them!\u201D But Moses and Aaron fell face down on the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Moses said to Aaron, \u201CQuick, take an incense burner and
        place burning coals on it from the altar. Lay incense on it, and carry it
        out among the people to purify them and make them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.[COMMENT[0]]
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s anger is blazing against them\u2014the
        plague has already begun.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:46 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: to make atonement for them.
    - title: 
      content: 'Aaron did as Moses told him and ran out among the people. The plague
        had already begun to strike down the people, but Aaron burned the incense
        and purified[COMMENT[0]] the people. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:47 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: and made atonement for.
    - title: 
      content: 'He stood between the dead and the living, and the plague stopped. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But 14,700 people died in that plague, in addition to those who had
        died in the affair involving Korah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Then because the plague had stopped, Aaron returned to Moses at the
        entrance of the Tabernacle.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The Budding of Aaron\u2019s Staff"
      content: '  [COMMENT[1]]Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '17:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 17:1-13 are numbered 17:16-28 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTell the people of Israel to bring you twelve wooden staffs,
        one from each leader of Israel\u2019s ancestral tribes, and inscribe each
        leader\u2019s name on his staff. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Inscribe Aaron\u2019s name on the staff of the tribe of Levi, for
        there must be one staff for the leader of each ancestral tribe. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Place these staffs in the Tabernacle in front of the Ark containing
        the tablets of the Covenant,[COMMENT[0]] where I meet with you. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'in the Tent of Meeting before the Testimony. '
        - ft: "The Hebrew word for \u201Ctestimony\u201D refers to the terms of the "
