    - title: 
      content: 'A man who makes a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> or makes
        a pledge under oath must never break it. He must do exactly what he said
        he would do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a young woman makes a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        or a pledge under oath while she is still living at her father\u2019s home, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and her father hears of the vow or pledge and does not object to
        it, then all her vows and pledges will stand. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if her father refuses to let her fulfill the vow or pledge on
        the day he hears of it, then all her vows and pledges will become invalid.
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will forgive her because her father would
        not let her fulfill them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow suppose a young woman makes a vow or binds herself with
        an impulsive pledge and later marries. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If her husband learns of her vow or pledge and does not object on
        the day he hears of it, her vows and pledges will stand. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if her husband refuses to accept her vow or impulsive pledge
        on the day he hears of it, he nullifies her commitments, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will forgive her. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If, however, a woman is a widow or is divorced, she must fulfill
        all her vows and pledges.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose a woman is married and living in her husband\u2019s
        home when she makes a vow or binds herself with a pledge. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If her husband hears of it and does not object to it, her vow or
        pledge will stand. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if her husband refuses to accept it on the day he hears of it,
        her vow or pledge will be nullified, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will forgive her. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So her husband may either confirm or nullify any vows or pledges
        she makes to deny herself. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if he does not object on the day he hears of it, then he is agreeing
        to all her vows and pledges. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If he waits more than a day and then tries to nullify a vow or pledge,
        he will be punished for her guilt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: These are the regulations the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Moses
        concerning relationships between a man and his wife, and between a father
        and a young daughter who still lives at home.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Conquest of the Midianites
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COn behalf of the people of Israel, take revenge on the Midianites
        for leading them into idolatry. After that, you will die and join your ancestors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses said to the people, \u201CChoose some men, and arm them
        to fight the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s war of revenge against
        Midian. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From each tribe of Israel, send 1,000 men into battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they chose 1,000 men from each tribe of Israel, a total of 12,000
        men armed for battle. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Moses sent them out, 1,000 men from each tribe, and Phinehas
        son of Eleazar the priest led them into battle. They carried along the holy
        objects of the sanctuary and the trumpets for sounding the charge. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They attacked Midian as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        Moses, and they killed all the men. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All five of the Midianite kings\u2014Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba\u2014died
        in the battle. They also killed Balaam son of Beor with the sword.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Israelite army captured the Midianite women and children
        and seized their cattle and flocks and all their wealth as plunder. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They burned all the towns and villages where the Midianites had lived. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After they had gathered the plunder and captives, both people and
        animals, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they brought them all to Moses and Eleazar the priest, and to the
        whole community of Israel, which was camped on the plains of Moab beside
        the Jordan River, across from Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Moses, Eleazar the priest, and all the leaders of the community went
        to meet them outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But Moses was furious with all the generals and captains[COMMENT[0]]
        who had returned from the battle.  '
      comments:
