    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy have you let all the women live?\u201D he demanded. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThese are the very ones who followed Balaam\u2019s advice and
        caused the people of Israel to rebel against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at Mount Peor. They are the ones who caused the plague to strike the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So kill all the boys and all the women who have had intercourse with
        a man. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Only the young girls who are virgins may live; you may keep them
        for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all of you who have killed anyone or touched a dead body must
        stay outside the camp for seven days. You must purify yourselves and your
        captives on the third and seventh days. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Purify all your clothing, too, and everything made of leather, goat
        hair, or wood.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Eleazar the priest said to the men who were in the battle, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given Moses this legal requirement: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anything made of gold, silver, bronze, iron, tin, or lead\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that is, all metals that do not burn\u2014must be passed through
        fire in order to be made ceremonially pure. These metal objects must then
        be further purified with the water of purification. But everything that burns
        must be purified by the water alone. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "On the seventh day you must wash your clothes and be purified. Then
        you may return to the camp.\u201D  "
      comments: []
