    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has conquered this whole area for
        the community of Israel, and it is ideally suited for all our livestock. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If we have found favor with you, please let us have this land as
        our property instead of giving us land across the Jordan River.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo you intend to stay here while your brothers go across and
        do all the fighting?\u201D Moses asked the men of Gad and Reuben. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy do you want to discourage the rest of the people of Israel
        from going across to the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given them? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your ancestors did the same thing when I sent them from Kadesh-barnea
        to explore the land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After they went up to the valley of Eshcol and explored the land,
        they discouraged the people of Israel from entering the land the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was giving them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was very angry with them, and
        he vowed, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Of all those I rescued from Egypt, no one who is twenty years
        old or older will ever see the land I swore to give to Abraham, Isaac, and
        Jacob, for they have not obeyed me wholeheartedly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The only exceptions are Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and
        Joshua son of Nun, for they have wholeheartedly followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with Israel and made
        them wander in the wilderness for forty years until the entire generation
        that sinned in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s sight had died. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But here you are, a brood of sinners, doing exactly the same thing!
        You are making the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> even angrier with Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you turn away from him like this and he abandons them again in
        the wilderness, you will be responsible for destroying this entire nation!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But they approached Moses and said, \u201CWe simply want to build
        pens for our livestock and fortified towns for our wives and children. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then we will arm ourselves and lead our fellow Israelites into battle
        until we have brought them safely to their land. Meanwhile, our families
        will stay in the fortified towns we build here, so they will be safe from
        any attacks by the local people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We will not return to our homes until all the people of Israel have
        received their portions of land. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But we do not claim any of the land on the other side of the Jordan.
        We would rather live here on the east side and accept this as our grant of
        land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CIf you keep your word and arm yourselves for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s battles, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and if your troops cross the Jordan and keep fighting until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has driven out his enemies, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then you may return when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has conquered
        the land. You will have fulfilled your duty to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and to the rest of the people of Israel. And the land on the east side of
        the Jordan will be your property from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you fail to keep your word, then you will have sinned against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, and you may be sure that your sin will
        find you out. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go ahead and build towns for your families and pens for your flocks,
        but do everything you have promised.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the men of Gad and Reuben replied, \u201CWe, your servants,
        will follow your instructions exactly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our children, wives, flocks, and cattle will stay here in the towns
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But all who are able to bear arms will cross over to fight for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, just as you have said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses gave orders to Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and
        the leaders of the clans of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u201CThe men of Gad and Reuben who are armed for battle
        must cross the Jordan with you to fight for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.
        If they do, give them the land of Gilead as their property when the land
        is conquered. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if they refuse to arm themselves and cross over with you, then
        they must accept land with the rest of you in the land of Canaan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The tribes of Gad and Reuben said again, \u201CWe are your servants,
        and we will do as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We will cross the Jordan into Canaan fully armed to fight for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, but our property will be here on this side
        of the Jordan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses assigned land to the tribes of Gad, Reuben, and half the
        tribe of Manasseh son of Joseph. He gave them the territory of King Sihon
        of the Amorites and the land of King Og of Bashan\u2014the whole land with
        its cities and surrounding lands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of Gad built the towns of Dibon, Ataroth, Aroer, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Atroth-shophan, Jazer, Jogbehah, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Beth-nimrah, and Beth-haran. These were all fortified towns with
        pens for their flocks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of Reuben built the towns of Heshbon, Elealeh, Kiriathaim, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nebo, Baal-meon, and Sibmah. They changed the names of some of the
        towns they conquered and rebuilt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the descendants of Makir of the tribe of Manasseh went to Gilead
        and conquered it, and they drove out the Amorites living there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Moses gave Gilead to the Makirites, descendants of Manasseh, and
        they settled there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Jair, another clan of the tribe of Manasseh, captured
        many of the towns in Gilead and changed the name of that region to the Towns
        of Jair.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:41 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Havvoth-jair.
    - title: 
      content: Meanwhile, a man named Nobah captured the town of Kenath and its surrounding
        villages, and he renamed that area Nobah after himself.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Remembering Israel\u2019s Journey"
      content: 'This is the route the Israelites followed as they marched out of
        Egypt under the leadership of Moses and Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s direction, Moses kept
        a written record of their progress. These are the stages of their march,
        identified by the different places where they stopped along the way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They set out from the city of Rameses in early spring\u2014on the
        fifteenth day of the first month[COMMENT[0]]\u2014on the morning after the
        first Passover celebration. The people of Israel left defiantly, in full
        view of all the Egyptians. "
      comments:
      - number: '33:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late March,
            April, or early May.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the Egyptians were burying all their firstborn sons, whom
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had killed the night before. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had defeated the gods of Egypt that night with great acts of judgment!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After leaving Rameses, the Israelites set up camp at Succoth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they left Succoth and camped at Etham on the edge of the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Etham and turned back toward Pi-hahiroth, opposite Baal-zephon,
        and camped near Migdol.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Pi-hahiroth[COMMENT[0]] and crossed the Red Sea[COMMENT[1]]
        into the wilderness beyond. Then they traveled for three days into the Etham
        wilderness and camped at Marah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:8a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in many Hebrew manuscripts, Samaritan Pentateuch, and Latin Vulgate
            (see also 33:7); most Hebrew manuscripts read '
          body: left from in front of Hahiroth.
      - number: '33:8b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: the sea.
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Marah and camped at Elim, where there were twelve springs
        of water and seventy palm trees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Elim and camped beside the Red Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:10 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'sea of reeds; '
        - ft: also in 33:11.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'They left the Red Sea and camped in the wilderness of Sin.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
