      content: 'They left Rissah and camped at Kehelathah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Kehelathah and camped at Mount Shepher.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Mount Shepher and camped at Haradah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Haradah and camped at Makheloth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Makheloth and camped at Tahath.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Tahath and camped at Terah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Terah and camped at Mithcah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Mithcah and camped at Hashmonah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Hashmonah and camped at Moseroth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Moseroth and camped at Bene-jaakan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Bene-jaakan and camped at Hor-haggidgad.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Hor-haggidgad and camped at Jotbathah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Jotbathah and camped at Abronah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Abronah and camped at Ezion-geber.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Ezion-geber and camped at Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Kadesh and camped at Mount Hor, at the border of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While they were at the foot of Mount Hor, Aaron the priest was directed
        by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to go up the mountain, and there he died.
        This happened in midsummer, on the first day of the fifth month[COMMENT[0]]
        of the fortieth year after Israel\u2019s departure from Egypt. "
      comments:
      - number: '33:38 '
        contents:
        - ft: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in July or August.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Aaron was 123 years old when he died there on Mount Hor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At that time the Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the Negev in
        the land of Canaan, heard that the people of Israel were approaching his
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the Israelites left Mount Hor and camped at Zalmonah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they left Zalmonah and camped at Punon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Punon and camped at Oboth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Oboth and camped at Iye-abarim on the border of Moab.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Iye-abarim[COMMENT[0]] and camped at Dibon-gad.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:45 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'As in 33:44; Hebrew reads '
          body: 'Iyim, '
        - ft: another name for Iye-abarim.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Dibon-gad and camped at Almon-diblathaim.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They left Almon-diblathaim and camped in the mountains east of the
        river,[COMMENT[0]] near Mount Nebo.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:47 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'the mountains of Abarim; '
        - ft: also in 33:48.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'They left the mountains east of the river and camped on the plains
        of Moab beside the Jordan River, across from Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Along the Jordan River they camped from Beth-jeshimoth as far as
        the meadows of Acacia[COMMENT[0]] on the plains of Moab.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:49 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: as far as Abel-shittim.
    - title: 
      content: 'While they were camped near the Jordan River on the plains of Moab
        opposite Jericho, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel: When
        you cross the Jordan River into the land of Canaan, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you must drive out all the people living there. You must destroy
        all their carved and molten images and demolish all their pagan shrines. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Take possession of the land and settle in it, because I have given
        it to you to occupy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must distribute the land among the clans by sacred lot and in
        proportion to their size. A larger portion of land will be allotted to each
        of the larger clans, and a smaller portion will be allotted to each of the
        smaller clans. The decision of the sacred lot is final. In this way, the
        portions of land will be divided among your ancestral tribes. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you fail to drive out the people who live in the land, those
        who remain will be like splinters in your eyes and thorns in your sides.
        They will harass you in the land where you live. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I will do to you what I had planned to do to them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Boundaries of the Land
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive these instructions to the Israelites: When you come into
        the land of Canaan, which I am giving you as your special possession, these
        will be the boundaries. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The southern portion of your country will extend from the wilderness
        of Zin, along the edge of Edom. The southern boundary will begin on the east
        at the Dead Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'Salt Sea; '
        - ft: also in 34:12.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'It will then run south past Scorpion Pass[COMMENT[0]] in the direction
        of Zin. Its southernmost point will be Kadesh-barnea, from which it will
        go to Hazar-addar, and on to Azmon. '
      comments:
      - number: '34:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the ascent of Akrabbim.
    - title: 
      content: 'From Azmon the boundary will turn toward the Brook of Egypt and end
        at the Mediterranean Sea.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: 'the sea; '
        - ft: also in 34:6, 7.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour western boundary will be the coastline of the Mediterranean
        Sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour northern boundary will begin at the Mediterranean Sea
        and run east to Mount Hor, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then to Lebo-hamath, and on through Zedad '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and Ziphron to Hazar-enan. This will be your northern boundary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe eastern boundary will start at Hazar-enan and run south
        to Shepham, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then down to Riblah on the east side of Ain. From there the boundary
        will run down along the eastern edge of the Sea of Galilee,[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: Sea of Kinnereth.
    - title: 
      content: "and then along the Jordan River to the Dead Sea. These are the boundaries
        of your land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Moses told the Israelites, \u201CThis territory is the homeland
        you are to divide among yourselves by sacred lot. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has commanded that the land be divided among the nine and a half remaining
        tribes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The families of the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and half the tribe of
        Manasseh have already received their grants of land '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "on the east side of the Jordan River, across from Jericho toward
        the sunrise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Leaders to Divide the Land
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEleazar the priest and Joshua son of Nun are the men designated
        to divide the grants of land among the people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Enlist one leader from each tribe to help them with the task. '
