  - verses:
    - title: Towns for the Levites
      content: 'While Israel was camped beside the Jordan on the plains of Moab across
        from Jericho, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCommand the people of Israel to give to the Levites from their
        property certain towns to live in, along with the surrounding pasturelands. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These towns will be for the Levites to live in, and the surrounding
        lands will provide pasture for their cattle, flocks, and other livestock. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The pastureland assigned to the Levites around these towns will extend
        1,500 feet[COMMENT[0]] from the town walls in every direction. '
      comments:
      - number: '35:4 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '1,000 cubits '
        - ft: '[460 meters].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "Measure off 3,000 feet[COMMENT[0]] outside the town walls in every
        direction\u2014east, south, west, north\u2014with the town at the center.
        This area will serve as the larger pastureland for the towns.  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: '2,000 cubits '
        - ft: '[920 meters].'
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSix of the towns you give the Levites will be cities of refuge,
        where a person who has accidentally killed someone can flee for safety. In
        addition, give them forty-two other towns. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In all, forty-eight towns with the surrounding pastureland will be
        given to the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These towns will come from the property of the people of Israel.
        The larger tribes will give more towns to the Levites, while the smaller
        tribes will give fewer. Each tribe will give property in proportion to the
        size of its land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Cities of Refuge
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\n\t\u201CWhen
        you cross the Jordan into the land of Canaan, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'designate cities of refuge to which people can flee if they have
        killed someone accidentally. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "These cities will be places of protection from a dead person\u2019s
        relatives who want to avenge the death. The slayer must not be put to death
        before being tried by the community. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Designate six cities of refuge for yourselves, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'three on the east side of the Jordan River and three on the west
        in the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These cities are for the protection of Israelites, foreigners living
        among you, and traveling merchants. Anyone who accidentally kills someone
        may flee there for safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if someone strikes and kills another person with a piece
        of iron, it is murder, and the murderer must be executed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Or if someone with a stone in his hand strikes and kills another
        person, it is murder, and the murderer must be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Or if someone strikes and kills another person with a wooden object,
        it is murder, and the murderer must be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The victim\u2019s nearest relative is responsible for putting the
        murderer to death. When they meet, the avenger must put the murderer to death. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So if someone hates another person and waits in ambush, then pushes
        him or throws something at him and he dies, it is murder. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Or if someone hates another person and hits him with a fist and he
        dies, it is murder. In such cases, the avenger must put the murderer to death
        when they meet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suppose someone pushes another person without having shown
        previous hostility, or throws something that unintentionally hits another
        person, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or accidentally drops a huge stone on someone, though they were not
        enemies, and the person dies. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If this should happen, the community must follow these regulations
        in making a judgment between the slayer and the avenger, the victim\u2019s
        nearest relative: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The community must protect the slayer from the avenger and must escort
        the slayer back to live in the city of refuge to which he fled. There he
        must remain until the death of the high priest, who was anointed with the
        sacred oil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut if the slayer ever leaves the limits of the city of refuge, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and the avenger finds him outside the city and kills him, it will
        not be considered murder. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The slayer should have stayed inside the city of refuge until the
        death of the high priest. But after the death of the high priest, the slayer
        may return to his own property. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These are legal requirements for you to observe from generation to
        generation, wherever you may live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll murderers must be put to death, but only if evidence is
        presented by more than one witness. No one may be put to death on the testimony
        of only one witness. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Also, you must never accept a ransom payment for the life of someone
        judged guilty of murder and subject to execution; murderers must always be
        put to death. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And never accept a ransom payment from someone who has fled to a
        city of refuge, allowing a slayer to return to his property before the death
        of the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This will ensure that the land where you live will not be polluted,
        for murder pollutes the land. And no sacrifice except the execution of the
        murderer can purify the land from murder.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '35:33 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: can make atonement for murder.
    - title: 
      content: "You must not defile the land where you live, for I live there myself.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, who lives among the people of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Women Who Inherit Property
      content: "Then the heads of the clans of Gilead\u2014descendants of Makir,
        son of Manasseh, son of Joseph\u2014came to Moses and the family leaders
        of Israel with a petition. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said, \u201CSir, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> instructed
        you to divide the land by sacred lot among the people of Israel. You were
        told by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to give the grant of land owned by
        our brother Zelophehad to his daughters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if they marry men from another tribe, their grants of land will
        go with them to the tribe into which they marry. In this way, the total area
        of our tribal land will be reduced. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then when the Year of Jubilee comes, their portion of land will be
        added to that of the new tribe, causing it to be lost forever to our ancestral
        tribe.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Moses gave the Israelites this command from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t:
        \u201CThe claim of the men of the tribe of Joseph is legitimate. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commands concerning
        the daughters of Zelophehad: Let them marry anyone they like, as long as
        it is within their own ancestral tribe. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'None of the territorial land may pass from tribe to tribe, for all
        the land given to each tribe must remain within the tribe to which it was
        first allotted. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The daughters throughout the tribes of Israel who are in line to
        inherit property must marry within their tribe, so that all the Israelites
        will keep their ancestral property. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No grant of land may pass from one tribe to another; each tribe of
        Israel must keep its allotted portion of land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The daughters of Zelophehad did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mahlah, Tirzah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Noah all married cousins on their
        father\u2019s side. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They married into the clans of Manasseh son of Joseph. Thus, their
        inheritance of land remained within their ancestral tribe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: These are the commands and regulations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave to the people of Israel through Moses while they were camped on the
        plains of Moab beside the Jordan River, across from Jericho.
      comments: []
